In line with this anti-discrimination strategy is also the current plan that Palmisan at the helm of IBM will be replaced by a woman next year – by Virginia Rometty.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and has so far held the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
In recent years, IBM has been conducting so-called online brainstorming, which has resulted in many future strategies and innovations.
No wonder - there are enough ideas, in the company almost half a million people are employed.
An institution with a good reputation
Their unshakable position in the business guarantees the company a strong image, both internally and externally.
“From the beginning, IBM had the concept of an institution rather than a mere technology company,” said Harvard Business School professor and author of a book about IBM, Rosabeth Moss Kanter.
“IBM is not a technology company, but a company that helps solve business problems using technology,” added George Colony of consulting firm Forrester Research.
As the company itself emphasizes, it is a difference to be only present in the market or to shape it directly through this presence.
IBM - in the states of its logo called "Big Blue" because of its family name, has grown into one of the largest companies in the world in a century.
