If modern post-war architecture, clear shapes, glass halls, bold twists and new building materials, which are typical of the belief in technical progress, are warmed up, then the Austrian pavilion of the architect Karl Schwanzer is a fitting and famous example for the Brüssler World Exhibition 1958.
