Occupied house where huge parties were held has been cleared
The homeowners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on Balmes street No. 51 (Barcelona).
The 12 housekeepers left the building yesterday afternoon without having resisted.
Everything indicates that the nightmares of the neighbors of house No. 51 on Balmes Street have come to an end.
Twelve people voluntarily left yesterday at noon the building which they had illegally occupied and where they had organized huge festivals that had driven the neighborhood to despair. The eviction took place on the basis of a court order without any police intervention.
After the eviction, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be controlled," the house manager confirmed.
The housekeepers, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the rest were inhabited - took the entire electrical system and part of the water supply with them, and they had painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans with alcoholic drinks.
In the three lower floors, huge parties were celebrated that lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also carried damage from it.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europa Press that her business had declined by 80% since the beginning of the house occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the housekeepers made their unfair competition, because they sold the drinks for three euros, while these in the discotheque cost 10 euros.
In addition, the owner of the leisure venue had been reported by the neighbors for disturbance of rest, while according to her statement the noise did not originate from the visitors of the disco, but from the housekeepers and especially from the guests of the festivals that were organized there, and which according to the statements of the angry neighbors in the last weeks became more and more longer.
The manager of the discotheque said the harassment was so great that she agreed with the owner of the building that she would not have to pay rent for the last nine months.
The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that it has received more complaints from neighbors in recent weeks.
The chairman of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in the Barcelona City Council, Alberto Fernández D<0xC3><0xAD>az, had demanded last week to immediately clear the building and to deal with the problems of bourgeois coexistence and the downfall of the district.
He explained that before the summer, only one floor of the building had been occupied, but that the housekeepers had penetrated into all floors of the building and almost all apartments in recent months.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to intervene against the asocial actions in the building."
Yesterday, another building in the Nou Barris neighborhood was cleared by the Catalan police.
At 3.30 p.m., police approached Montral Street 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who had watched four people attempting to enter the building.
The four were immediately arrested.
