The booklet described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
It was even compared in numbers to New York’s Central Park.
With the fall of the CMB in 1987, the park became the upper limit of Barcelona in the eyes of many, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that does not spread in the north-south direction, but upwards (mountains) and downwards (sea).
Collserola’s classification as a nature park plays with this idea.
Yellowstone was no longer used as a model for Central Park, but rather for Yellowstone with wild pigs in the role of the yogi bear.
