Why does the unemployment rate of disabled workers remain at such a high level?
About 19% of people with disabilities are looking for a job.
Today begins the "15th Week of Work for the Disabled".
Despite a targeted public policy introduced in 2005, the unemployment rate among disabled people is always twice the average: 19% versus 9% unemployment of the total population.
Discouraging?
“No,” stressed <0xC3><0x89>ric Blanchet, Director General of the Adapt Association, which organizes the “Week of Work for the Disabled.”
